node.text: Save my recipe for Poached Salmon Soup also known as Vietnamese Canh Chua. The ingredients are 5 cups of water, 3 salmon filets, 1 tsp. Salt, 1 tbsp. Fish sauce, 1/2 tbsp. Sugar, 1/2 onion, 1 cup pineapple, 2 tomatoes, 1/2 packet of Knorr tamarind powder, 1 oz sliced green onions and 1 oz chopped cilantro. Serve over rice or if you’re doing low carb eat it ok it’s own. It’s the perfect healthy dinner and the salmon comes out moist and flakey. @staub_usa #canhchua #vietnamesefood #vietnameserecipes #sinigang #asianfood #asianrecipes #healthyrecipe #easyrecipes #dinnerideas #cookingvideo

node.title: Making Poached Salmon Sour Soup aka Vietnamese Canh Chua

node.text: Save my recipe for for Shrimp Papaya Salad! It’s about 4 cups of shredded green papaya, 3 Thai chilies, 3 cloves of garlic, 1 tbsp. Shrimp paste, 1 tbsp. Sugar, 1 tbsp Fish sauce, juice of 3 limes, 1 cup sliced cherry tomatoes and 1/4 cup chopped cilantro. Top with boiled shrimp and peanuts. @zwilling_usa #shrimppapayasalad #papayasalad #greenpapaya #thairecipes #thaifood #asianrecipes #saladrecipe #lunchideas #recipevideo #livecooking #cookingvideo

Save my recipe for One Pan Tomato Pasta and Pasta Chips with @feelgoodfoodie. Start with olive oil, garlic and onions and then add grape tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Smash tomatoes and then mix in pasta and pasta water. Top with basil and Parmesan cheese. @henckels_usa @staub_usa

node.text:
Save my recipe Vietnamese Pork and Mango Rolls. The pork loin is seasoned with lemongrass, oyster sauce, fish sauce, thick soy sauce and brown sugar. I then assembled my spring rolls with rice paper, pork, red butter lettuce, cucumber, mint and mango. The peanut sauce is peanut butter, hoisin sauce and milk. #springrolls 
#porkloin #vietnameserecipes #vietnamesefood #vietnamesecuisine #vietnamesespringrolls #peanutsauce #easyrecipes #lunchideas #appetizers #recipeoftheday #healthyrecipes

node.text: Save my recipe for Chicken Teriyaki with Asparagus & Rice! It’s a delicious dinner that can be made in under 20 minutes. I seasoned 6 chicken thighs with salt and seared both sides in avocado oil. Then marinade was 1/2 cup yoshida’s sauce, 1/2 cup water, 1 tbsp. minced ginger, 1 tbsp. minced garlic, 1oz sliced green onion and 1/2 tsp. Black pepper. #teriyakichicken #teriyaki #asianrecipes #easydinner #dinnerideas #chickenrecipes #chickenandrice #recipeoftheday #recipeshare #homecooking #livecooking

node.text: Save my recipe for Spicy Peanut Noodles! I used fresh udon noodles that I got from the Asian Market, but you substitute with any noodles you like. The sauce was sesame oil, soy sauce, black vinegar, peanut butter powder, brown sugar, sesame seeds and green onions. Toss in the cooked noodles and add a little water from the pot. Mix everything and then top with chili oil. #spicynoodles #noodles #noodle #asianrecipes #asianfood #simplerecipes #easyrecipes #lunchideas #dinnerideas #recipeshare #peanut #peanutbutter #peanutbutterlover

node.text: Save my recipe for Sesame Crusted Tuna with a Teriyaki Glaze! I made this recipe in Partnership with @samsclub for #aapiheritagemonth. The ingredients are yellowfin tuna, roasted sesame seeds, Yoshida’s marinade, garlic, ginger, avocado, roasted seaweed with rice. All ingredients sourced at @samsclub #samspartner #ahituna #tunabowl #asianrecipes #healthyrecipes #lunchideas #dinnerideas

node.text: My parents have not seen my brother @le_37 in over a year. He flew in today from SoCal and we pranked my parents. I told them people were coming to inspect the new house, but it was really my brother in a Hazmat Suit. Throughout the years we’ve had many surprises where my brother will just pop up. One time my parents were asleep any my brother came in and placed my 6 month old nephew in their arms. I wish we had footage of all the surprises throughout the years, but this one was the best by far! #prank #pranks #prankster #reunitedanditfeelssogood #familyreunion #reunited #familyovereverything #hiddencamera #family

node.title: My brother surprised my parents in a Hazmat Suit

node.text: How to make Vietnamese Shrimp Spring Rolls with Homemade Peanut Sauce. Ingredients are rice paper, red leaf lettuce, cucumbers, cilantro, bean sprouts or rice noodles. For the sauce it’s equal parts peanut sauce, hoisin sauce and slowly whisk in milk until you reach the right consistency. #vietnamesefood #vietnamesecuisine #vietnameserecipes #shrimprecipes #springrolls #springroll #ricepaper #eggrolls #peanutsauce #vietnameseapringrolls #easyrecipes #easymeals #healthyrecipeshare #healthyrecipes #lunchideas #appetizers #snackideas

node.text: You guys know I’ve been on a hunt for Chamoy and I finally found it! I had to recreate the Mexican Fruit Cup I had in LA. I added watermelon, cucumber, pineapple, orange, mango, lime juice, tajin and Chamoy. How did I do guys?! What else should I add next? @henckels_usa #chamoy #mexicanfruit #fruitbowl #summerrecipes #healthyfood #healthyrecipes #snackideas #healthysnacks #fruit #fruitsalad #easyrecipes

node.text: Save and Share my recipe for Fire Cracker Salmon! It’s so easy to make! Simply fry some salmon, wrap in rice paper and green onions and fry again until crispy. The sauce is 1 tbsp soy sauce, 1 tbsp sesame oil, 1 tsp white vinegar, 1 tsp brown sugar and toss in some sesame seeds and cilantro. #firecrackersalmon #salmonrecipe #salmonroll #ricepaper #asianrecipes #asianfood #appetizerideas #healthyrecipes #easyrecipes #cookingvideos

node.text: Save my recipe to make Whole Fried Brie with Berries! Remember to cut cross cross on top, fry in a little olive oil on medium heat and cover with a lid. Mix strawberries, blueberries and raspberries with sugar and add to Brie. Cool for another minute covered and then sprinkle almonds. #friedbrie #brie #cheesey #cheeserecipes #cheesepull #appetizers #easyrecipes #appetizerideas #simplerecipes #recipevideo #cookingvideos #recipeshare

node.text: Save my recipe for Poached Salmon Soup also known as Vietnamese Canh Chua. The ingredients are 5 cups of water, 3 salmon filets, 1 tsp. Salt, 1 tbsp. Fish sauce, 1/2 tbsp. Sugar, 1/2 onion, 1 cup pineapple, 2 tomatoes, 1/2 packet of Knorr tamarind powder, 1 oz sliced green onions and 1 oz chopped cilantro. Serve over rice or if you’re doing low carb eat it ok it’s own. It’s the perfect healthy dinner and the salmon comes out moist and flakey. @staub_usa #canhchua #vietnamesefood #vietnameserecipes #sinigang #asianfood #asianrecipes #healthyrecipe #easyrecipes #dinnerideas #cookingvideo

node.text: My mom made this Salmon Tamarind Soup for me last week and everyone flooded my DM’s for the recipe so I asked her to film it next time she made it. She started with about 5 cups of water, 1 tsp. salt, 1 tbsp. fish sauce, 1 cup pineapple, half a small onion, 1 1/2oz tamarind paste, 2 roma tomatoes, 3 salmon filets, and fresh cilantro and Thai chilies. Simmer for about 5-7 minutes and the salmon will be tender and flaky. You can also substitute tamarind paste for Knorr tamarind soup mix. #tamarindsoup #tamarind #salmonsoup #salmondinner #salmonrecipe #vietnamesefood #vietnameserecipes #dinnerideas #easyrecipes #healthyrecipes

node.text: Save my recipe for Whole Fried Brie! It’s a perfect appetizer for a Summer movie night under the stars. We enjoyed it while going down memory lane watching old vacation videos with our outdoor movie theater from @samsclub . I fried the brie in avocado oil, added grape tomatoes, drizzled olive oil and a pinch of salt. I then covered with a lid and cooked for another 10 minutes. Last, I topped with chopped basil and drizzled balsamic glaze. #SamsPartner #SamsClubSummer #brie #friedbrie #movienight

node.text: Wow! What have I been missing my whole life?! I saw this fruit vendor in front of a gas station and made my husband stop. It was only $7 for this big cup. He put cucumbers, cantaloupe, a whole orange, pineapple and mango! He then topped it with Tajin, Chamoy and fresh lime juice. So glad we picked this up before driving home. I’m in fruit heaven! Definitely making this at home. Where can I find Chamoy?Thank you @emmagribbon for influencing me lol. #fruit #fruitinfluencer #fruithacks #fruitcup #fruitvendor #roadtripsnacks #tajin #chamoy

node.text: Want a Milk Tea for one dollar? Try this hack. McDonald’s Sweet Ice Tea with two creamers. I only drink this when I’m traveling as a treat because I can’t have too much caffeine, but it taste just like a milk tea to me. #milktea #mcdonaldsdrink #drinkhack #mcdonalds #foodhack #roadtrip #roadtripsnacks

node.text: I had so many tomatoes from my mother in law’s garden that I made a big batch of Tomato Basil Pasta. This was so good because the tomatoes were so sweet. Recipe is so simple and I didn’t measure anything. Just olive oil, a lot of garlic, tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil, pasta water and grated Parmesan. Honestly my favorite pasta because the ingredients are so fresh and simple. #pasta #pastarecipe #tomatobasil #tomatopasta #pastasauce #healthyrecipes #recipevideo #cookingvideos #pastalover #onepanmeal #easyrecipes #lunchideas

node.text: Save my recipe for Green Papaya Salad with Shrimp! It’s about 4-5 cups of shredded green papaya, 1 cup of cherry tomatoes, 1/4 cup chopped cilantro. The sauce is 4 cloves of garlic, 3 Thai chilies and 1/2 tbsp. Of shrimp paste. Grind everything together and add 1 tbsp. fish sauce, 1 -2 tbsp. Sugar and juice is 2-3 limes. You can add more of less of any of these ingredients depending on your taste preferences. I like mine more sour so I add more lime juice and less salty so less shrimp paste. Top with boiled shrimp and roasted peanuts #greenpapayasalad #greenpapaya #papaya #papayasalad #thaifood #thairecipes #asianfood #asianrecipes #saladrecipe #recipevideo #recipeoftheday
